## Shared Protocol

- User instructions override skill defaults.
- Report workflow status with exactly one of: `DONE`, `DONE_WITH_CONCERNS`, `BLOCKED`, `NEEDS_CONTEXT`.
- Escalate instead of guessing when requirements are missing, correctness is uncertain, or scope exceeds what can be verified.
- Process skills come before implementation skills.
- Classify the task before choosing controls:
  - `Tier 0`: ordinary work with no sensitive write path
  - `Tier 1`: important business or state-changing work without financial exposure
  - `Tier 2`: financial-sensitive work that affects billing, limits, payment state, or reconciliation inputs
  - `Tier 3`: money-moving or ledger-affecting work
- Apply only the controls that match the highest affected tier.
- If only one subflow is financially sensitive, isolate that subflow and apply the higher tier there instead of upgrading the whole task.

